[14/5/24, 11:50:55] Sofi: How to have an argument in a matured way?

Keep it private

Ensure that you don‚Äôt fight in front of people who aren‚Äôt relevant to the topic that you are arguing about. When a couple fights in front of their children, it‚Äôs not a very good idea. If you have a minor disagreement with a work colleague, you don‚Äôt have to express your dissatisfaction in front of a new employee.

Be specific

Don‚Äôt indulge in vague complaints. Say exactly what you aren‚Äôt very happy about. If you have an issue with the tardiness of an employee, let him know about that in exact words. If you put your point across very specifically, you also give the other person a chance to improve their behavior and let them know what is bothering you.

Don‚Äôt generalize

Generalizing in an argument or a fight is using words like ‚Äúnever‚Äù and ‚Äúalways‚Äù when accusing someone of anything. Statements like ‚Äúyou never help me‚Äù, ‚Äúyou always do it wrong‚Äù show that you don‚Äôt trust the other person. In fact, these kind of statements are also very discouraging and don‚Äôt give them an opportunity to learn from their mistakes.

Be relevant

Always deal with the topic at hand. Don‚Äôt talk about past mistakes and make the argument more dramatic. That way you can deal with problems more effectively and also help the other person improve whatever wrong he/she is doing.

No personal attacks

Refrain from making personal comments to hurt the person you are arguing with. If you do, you may lose your relationship with your friend, spouse or work colleague forever.

Remain calm

Take a time out to remain calm even when you are fighting. If you do this, people will take you more seriously and people will understand your view better. To remain calm you can go for a walk, write in a journal or do whatever it takes to maintain a certain level of peace even i the midst of all the anger and bitterness.

Set a time limit

Your disagreement doesn‚Äôt have to get over in a day or a week. It may take time and that‚Äôs okay. Don‚Äôt make yourself feel bad about it. It does take time for two people to understand each other‚Äôs views or opinions.

C√≥mo funciona:
Una empresa de outsourcing en Espa√±a se encarga de ser tu empleador legal.
La empresa suiza paga a esta intermediaria, que se encarga de gestionar tu salario, seguridad social e impuestos en Espa√±a.
Ventajas para la empresa:
Simplifica el proceso, ya que no necesita registrarse como empleador en Espa√±a.

Desventajas:

Costes aproximados:

Ejemplo: Si cobras 2,000 euros brutos al mes, la empresa pagar√≠a entre 2,200 y 2,300 euros.

¬øTe conviene?
Depende de tus objetivos:

¬øQui√©n es Sinterklaas?

Es representado como un anciano sabio con barba blanca, vestido con una capa roja de obispo, mitra y b√°culo dorado. ¬øQui√©n es Zwarte Piet?

Zwarte Piet (literalmente ‚ÄúPedro el Negro‚Äù) es el ayudante de Sinterklaas. Originalmente, Zwarte Piet era representado como una figura oscura con la cara pintada de negro, vestida con ropa colorida del estilo renacentista. Su rol tradicional era ayudar a Sinterklaas a repartir los regalos y dulces, trepar por las chimeneas y llevar un saco lleno de juguetes (o carb√≥n para los ni√±os desobedientes).

Controversia sobre Zwarte Piet

En los √∫ltimos a√±os, Zwarte Piet ha sido objeto de un intenso debate. La representaci√≥n cl√°sica con la cara pintada de negro ha sido criticada por ser racista y ofensiva, ya que muchos lo ven como un s√≠mbolo de estereotipos coloniales. Esto ha llevado a un cambio en la tradici√≥n en algunos lugares, donde ahora Zwarte Piet es representado como ‚ÄúPiet de Chimenea‚Äù (Roetveegpiet), con manchas de holl√≠n en la cara, explicando que su piel est√° sucia por trepar por las chimeneas.

Celebraci√≥n

La noche del 5 de diciembre, conocida como ‚ÄúPakjesavond‚Äù (Noche de los regalos), es el momento culminante de la celebraci√≥n. Las familias intercambian regalos, que a menudo van acompa√±ados de poemas humor√≠sticos o bromas sobre la persona que recibe el regalo. Tambi√©n es com√∫n comer dulces tradicionales como pepernoten, speculaas y chocolate en forma de letras iniciales.
